article.headline: Kent St. 69, Toledo 49
article.story: TOLEDO, Ohio -- Justin Greene and Tyree Evans scored 14 points each to lead Kent State to a 69-49 victory over Toledo on Tuesday night. The Golden Flashes (13-7, 4-2 Mid-American Conference) shot 50 percent from the field (26-for-52) and hit eight 3-pointers to win their third consecutive game. Kent State led 24-21 when it went on a 20-0 run that spanned both halves. The Golden Flashes finished the first half on an 8-0 streak and then opened the second half with a 12-0 surge that increased the advantage to 44-21 with 16:36 to play. Greene, who also had eight rebounds, scored nine of Kent State's 20 points and Toledo (3-17, 0-6) was scoreless for 7:05 during the run. Kent State outrebounded Toledo, which has lost 11 straight games, 31-21. Jake Barnett scored 15 points to lead Toledo, which shot 33.3 percent from the field (8-for-24) in the first half.
